text.paragraph:
Extrapyramidal symptoms, such as pseudo-parkinsonism, akathisia and dystonia have been reported (see 
                                    Dystonia: Class Effect
                                 ). Management of these extrapyramidal symptoms depends upon the type and severity. Rapid relief of acute symptoms may require the use of an injectable antiparkinson agent. More slowly emerging symptoms may be managed by reducing the dosage of thiothixene and/or administering an oral antiparkinson agent.
